title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Auf der anderen Seite
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Vivre sa vie: Film en douze tableaux
overview: Twelve episodic tales in the life of a Parisian woman and her slow descent into prostitution.

title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: Ivanovo detstvo
overview: In WW2, twelve year old Soviet orphan Ivan Bondarev works for the Soviet army as a scout behind the German lines and strikes a friendship with three sympathetic Soviet officers.

title: Y tu mamá también
overview: In Mexico, two teenage boys and an attractive older woman embark on a road trip and learn a thing or two about life, friendship, sex, and each other.
stars: ['Maribel Verdú', 'Gael García Bernal', 'Daniel Giménez Cacho', 'Ana López Mercado']

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: Gran Torino
overview: Disgruntled Korean War veteran Walt Kowalski sets out to reform his neighbor, Thao Lor, a Hmong teenager who tried to steal Kowalski's prized possession: a 1972 Gran Torino.

title: Rebel Without a Cause
overview: A rebellious young man with a troubled past comes to a new town, finding friends and enemies.

title: Cat on a Hot Tin Roof
overview: Brick is an alcoholic ex-football player who drinks his days away and resists the affections of his wife. A reunion with his terminal father jogs a host of memories and revelations for both father and son.

title: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
overview: A senator returns to a western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

title: Ordinary People
overview: The accidental death of the older son of an affluent family deeply strains the relationships among the bitter mother, the good-natured father, and the guilt-ridden younger son.

title: Platoon
overview: Chris Taylor, a neophyte recruit in Vietnam, finds himself caught in a battle of wills between two sergeants, one good and the other evil. A shrewd examination of the brutality of war and the duality of man in conflict.

title: Viskningar och rop
overview: When a woman dying of cancer in early twentieth-century Sweden is visited by her two sisters, long-repressed feelings between the siblings rise to the surface.

title: Full Metal Jacket
overview: A pragmatic U.S. Marine observes the dehumanizing effects the Vietnam War has on his fellow recruits from their brutal boot camp training to the bloody street fighting in Hue.

title: Forrest Gump
overview: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the events of Vietnam, Watergate and other historical events unfold through the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, whose only desire is to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Jules et Jim
overview: Decades of a love triangle concerning two friends and an impulsive woman.
